"Voutilainen A., Huuskonen H.","Long-term changes in the water quality and fish community of a large boreal lake affected by rising water temperatures and nutrient-rich sewage discharges - With special emphasis on the European perch",2010,"Knowledge and Management of Aquatic Ecosystems",,"397",,"03p1","03p14",,,10.1051/kmae/2010017,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-77955457204&partnerID=40&md5=83277adc2f81f7d174b04a31ad2bf328","Ecological Research Institute, University of Eastern Finland, P.O. Box 111, FI-80101 Joensuu, Finland","Voutilainen, A., Ecological Research Institute, University of Eastern Finland, P.O. Box 111, FI-80101 Joensuu, Finland; Huuskonen, H., Ecological Research Institute, University of Eastern Finland, P.O. Box 111, FI-80101 Joensuu, Finland","In this study, we report the changes in the water quality and fish community of a large boreal lake (Lake Pyhäselkä, Finland) in 1975-2005, when the lake was affected first by industrial and municipal sewage discharge and then by rising water temperatures. In the 1980s, the lake's trophic state proceeded from oligotrophic to mesotrophic, which favoured cyprinids. The increased cyprinid density strengthened the competition pressure on perch (Perca fluviatilis) reducing the growth rates of young perch. The lake's trophic state shifted from mesotrophic back to oligotrophic in the 1990s as a result of effective treatment of sewage waters. The water temperature in Lake Pyhäselkä rose from the beginning to the end of the monitoring period. The higher temperature favoured perch. In future, the warming may benefit pikeperch (Sander lucioperca) evenmore than perch. This will probably affect the perch population, as pikeperch prey effectively on perch. © 2010 ONEMA.","Eutrophication; Fish; Freshwater lake; Global warming; Pulp mill effluent","Cyprinidae; Perca fluviatilis; Sander lucioperca",,,,,,"Bagge, P., Hakkari, L., Effects of paper mill effluents on the fish fauna of stony shores of Lake Päijänne (1992) Hydrobiologia, 243-244, pp. 413-420; Bergman, E., Temperature-dependent differences in foraging ability of two percids, Perca fluviatilis and Gymnocephalus cernuus (1987) Environ. Biol. Fish., 19, pp. 45-53; Boisclair, D., Leggett, W.C., Among-population variability of fish growth: III. Influence of fish community (1989) Can. J. Fish. Aquat. Sci., 46, pp. 1539-1550; Boisclair, D., Leggett, W.C., Among-population variability of fish growth: II. Influence of prey type (1989) Can. J. Fish. Aquat. Sci., 46, pp. 468-482; Bolger, T., Connolly, P.L., The selection of suitable indices for the measurement and analysis of fish condition (1989) J. Fish Biol., 34, pp. 171-182; Dörner, H., Hülsmann, S., Hölker, F., Skov, C., Wagner, A., Size-dependent predator-prey relationships between pikeperch and their prey fish (2007) Ecol. Freshw. Fish, 16, pp. 307-314; Gyllström, M., Hansson, L.-A., Jeppesen, E., Garcia-Criado, F., Gross, E., Irvine, K., Kairesalo, T., Moss, B., The role of climate in shaping zooplankton communities of shallow lakes (2005) Limnol. Oceanogr., 50, pp. 2008-2021; Hakkari, L., Effects of pulp and paper mill effluents on fish populations in Finland (1992) Finnish Fish. Res., 13, pp. 93-106; Hakkari, L., Bagge, P., Reproductive success of Coregonus species in areas loaded by effluents from paper mills (1992) Hydrobiologia, 243-244, pp. 405-412; Hansson, S., Effects of pulp and paper mill effluents on coastal fish communities in the Gulf of Bothnia, Baltic Sea (1987) Ambio, 16, pp. 344-348; Helminen, H., Karjalainen, J., Kurkilahti, M., Rask, M., Sarvala, J., Eutrophication and fish biodiversity in Finnish lakes (2000) Verh. Internat. Verein. Limnol., 27, pp. 194-199; Hjelm, J., Persson, L., Christensen, B., Growth, morphological variation and ontogenetic niche shifts in perch (Perca fluviatilis) in relation to resource availability (2000) Oecologia, 122, pp. 190-199; Hokanson, K.E.F., Temperature requirements of some percids and adaptations to the s